          <sectionnumber>3</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Despite the requirements of section 2, within the boundaries of the following geographic locations, the installation of a new water closet or urinal in all occupancy classifications as described in the British Columbia Building Code must not exceed the flush cycle listed for that fixture in the table following paragraph (ll), titled Maximum Flush Cycle Table 2:</sectiontext>
